        public void setImagePath(java.lang.String imagePath)
        Sets the absolute path of the image file to be added as an annotation. The image must be a square image and the size must be a power of 2 ( 32x32, 64x64, etc).

      • setOffset

        public void setOffset(SKScreenPoint offset)
        Sets the offset for the annotation added using an image. Use this property for positioning the annotation image around the location. It has effect just when the annotation is added by giving an absolute path for the annotation or when adding it using SKAnnotationView , not by type.By default, the center of the image will coincide with the location.
        Parameters:
        offset -
